        1.a dynamic array of references (pointers)
        2.Python list implemented as a resizable dynamic array
        3.Internally, it uses contiguous block of memory
        4.Stores references to objects, not the objects themselves

        Python list: [10, "hello", 3.14]

        Memory layout:

        +-----------------------------+
        | ptr | ptr | ptr | empty ... |
        +-----------------------------+
           ↓     ↓      ↓
          10   "hello"  3.14
        We can access list using index cause it uses contiguous block of memory (CPU cache friendly)
